Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1-inch-thick half-moons.

Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary or trim and halve @?Brussels sprouts{} lengthwise. (Save carrots for another use.)

In a #medium bowl{} (use a large bowl for 4 servings), gently combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{3/4%tsp} (1 1/4 tsp for 4), and @pepper{}.

Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).

Place meatloaves on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Toss carrots on empty side with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets; roast meatloaves on middle rack and carrots on top rack.)

Roast on top rack until meatloaves are cooked through and carrots are browned and tender, ~{22-25%minutes}.

> Love extra-crispy veggies? Once meatloaves are done, remove from sheet and continue roasting carrots for 2-3 minutes more.

== Sumac Roasted Broccoli (or Brussels Sprouts) ==

Roast meatloaves on top rack for ~{5%minutes} (skip roasting carrots!), then remove sheet from oven. Swap in broccoli or Brussels sprouts for carrots; carefully toss with @sumac{1%tsp} as instructed. Roast ~{15-20%minutes} more.

== Creamy Caramelized Onion Sauce ==

While everything roasts, halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @?olive oil{} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes} (7-10 minutes for 4 servings). Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Add a large drizzle of oil to same pan over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{6-9%minutes}.

> Lower heat and add a splash of water if onion begins to brown too quickly.

Add @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup}, and @sugar{3/4%tsp} (1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) to pan with onion; cook until thickened, ~{1-3%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) and a pinch of chopped parsley. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Carefully toss zucchini and carrots together with half the sumac (all for 4 servings).

Divide meatloaves and carrots and zucchini between plates. Spoon caramelized onion sauce over meatloaves; garnish with remaining chopped parsley. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.